<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-07T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/353:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-07T19:00:00-05:00">March 7, 1934—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>15. Legation at Bucharest telegraphs that Rumanian Government has
                                granted a transit visa to Insull and that latter is expected in <pb facs="0670" n="570" xml:id="pg_570"/> Rumania within 48 hours.
                                The American Ministers at Bucharest, Sofia and Belgrade are being
                                instructed to request Insull’s provisional arrest and detention if
                                and when he enters the territory of the countries to which they are
                                respectively accredited.</p>
                            <p>Keep Department fully and promptly informed of developments.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>